This paper discusses the implementation of a synapse in a neural network, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of a floating-gate transistor, which is commonly used in electronic circuits and falls under the category of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the mathematical procedure used to obtain control voltages for the FG device, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the possible VLSI implementation of drain voltage waveform generator circuits, which falls under the category of VLSI design (cs.VLSI).
